body.p: Fraction absorbed, i.e., only a fraction of the captopril in the intestinal lumen is absorbed. This parameter determines how much of the captopril is excreted.
F_cap_abs of dose is absorbed. (1-F_cap_abs) is excreted in feces.

'Using radioactive labelled captopril in 3 volunteers 56 +- 6 % of a single dose was recovered in urine and 39 +- 5 % in the feces [6], indicating that almost 60% of the administered dose was absorbed. Absorption could be even higher because a proportion of the drug and its metabolites may also be excreted in the bile.'{Ball1987}

parameter.name: rate of captopril disulfide fecal excretion
